Start
/ Reading %!error.callback% inside an error handler resolves through
/ app.Errors.Current.Callback to a Data<ErrorCallback>.
- throw error "boom", on error call HandleErrorCallback
- assert %callbackSeen% is true, "on-error handler should have run and read callback"

HandleErrorCallback
- set %cb% = %!error.callback%
- assert %cb% is not null
- set %callbackSeen% = true
